{"履修期": "春学期", "主な教授言語": "英語", "授業目的": "This course is more advanced than English Communication A/B/C/D. Students should have already completed Contemporary Topics 1. The objectives of this course are:1. To develop students’ English proficiency through the study of academic topics in the field of sociology.2. To build students’ confidence in using English as a communicative tool.3. To help students improve their listening and note-taking skills through extensive lecture-listening activities.4. To introduce students to significant vocabulary words relevant to a wide range of academic topics.5. To prepare students to actively take part in discussions, teaching them the fundamental skills for agreeing and disagreeing with others’ opinions.", "到達目標": "1. Students will develop their academic skills.2. Students will become more confident and effective communicators.3. Students will strengthen their listening comprehension, note-taking and discussion skills.4. Students will acquire new vocabulary that will enhance their academic achievement.", "特記事項": "", "関連科目": "<span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:;\">English Communication Advanced D (01-09)</span>", "授業の概要・背景": "", "授業方法": "1. This course will be conducted in English only and English will be the means of communication between the students and the instructor.&nbsp; (Students will also be expected to communicate with one another in English.)2.&nbsp; Students are encouraged to actively participate in class discussions, both independently and collaboratively, in order to enhance their competence and confidence in English and also to create a better learning environment for all.", "トピック": {"第1回": ["<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin:0cm;\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" times=\"times\" new=\"new\" roman\",serif;\"=\"roman',serif;'\" style=\"font-family:Cambria,serif;font-size:11pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:14.6667px;\">【</span>Startup Week</span><s